        <p style="margin-top: 24px;">See also: <a href="/alternatives/surfer-seo/" class="accent">Surfer SEO alternatives</a>, <a href="/modules/content-seo/" class="accent">Content SEO module</a>, or <a href="/pricing/" class="accent">theStacc pricing</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is Surfer SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">A content optimization platform that analyzes top-ranking pages via NLP and TF-IDF algorithms, providing a real-time score as you write to indicate which terms and structures improve Google ranking potential. Founded 2017, acquired by Groupe Positive in 2025.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does Surfer SEO cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">$119/month (Standard), $219/month (Pro), $359/month (Peace of Mind) on monthly billing. Annual plans are roughly 17% cheaper. No free trial — you pay before you test.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is there a free version of Surfer SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No free version. The Keyword Surfer Chrome extension gives free basic search volume data, but the full Content Editor — the reason most people buy Surfer — requires a paid plan from $119/month.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Surfer SEO write content for you?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Surfer AI generates first drafts on Pro and Peace of Mind plans, but outputs need 30–60 minutes of editing. The platform doesn't auto-publish to websites. You still need writers and a CMS workflow.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is a good Surfer SEO content score?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Experienced users target 65–85, not 100. Chasing a perfect score usually means unnatural keyword stuffing that harms readability. The practical sweet spot is 70–80.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Surfer SEO do local SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">No. There are no local SEO features, no Google Business Profile tools, no citation management, and no Google Maps ranking capabilities. Local service businesses need a different tool.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Surfer SEO worth it for small businesses?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Only if you have writers. Real total cost including a writing team runs $2,500–$7,700/month. Done-for-you alternatives publish 30 articles for $99/month with no writers required.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What are the best Surfer SEO alternatives?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">For content optimization: Clearscope ($129/month), Frase.io ($49/month), MarketMuse ($149+/month). For done-for-you publishing without hiring writers: theStacc ($99/month, 30 auto-published articles, no writers needed).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Surfer SEO track AI search visibility?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes — as a paid add-on. The AI Visibility Tracker (~$95/month for 25 prompts) monitors your brand mentions across ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, and Google AI Overviews. It's one of the few tools in the category that does this.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How accurate is Surfer's keyword research?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Intentionally limited. Volume estimates skew high and difficulty scores are less reliable than Ahrefs or Semrush. Most teams pair Surfer with a dedicated keyword tool — which adds cost.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Who owns Surfer SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Founded in 2017 in Wrocław, Poland by brothers Michał and Lucjan Suski. Acquired by Groupe Positive in January 2025. The platform continues to operate independently under its own brand.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the Surfer SEO SERP Analyzer?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">A pre-writing research tool that deep-dives top-ranking pages for your target keyword, showing word counts, backlinks, heading counts, historical SERP changes, and mobile vs. desktop ranking differences. Available as an add-on (~$29/month).</div>
        </div>
      </div>
